• Prior to the review/evaluation, a copy of the draft mandate;

• A copy of the review/evaluation report.

5.3. Within three months of the end of the Fund's financial year, the Lead Donor will provide the Co-donor with the financial statements, indicating, as at the end of the preceding fiscal year, the funds received from the Co-donor, the funds paid into the Fund, and any contribution balance carried over to the following year. The financial statements will be in euros and indicate the sums received from the Co-donor in Danish Kroner. They will also indicate the sum paid into the Fund in the relevant currency, as well as its vaiue in euros. The financial statements will be balanced and reconciled in euros. Furthermore, the Lead Donor may provide the Co-donor with documentation relating to incoming and outgoing payments of funds provided by the Co-donor to the bank account mentioned in Paragraph 4(2) above.

5.4. The Lead Donor will not be responsible for any exchange rate losses or costs resulting from or related to the transfer of funds between the Co-donor and the Lead Donor, or between the Lead Donor and the Fund and vice versa.

Paragraph 6: Reservations 6.1. The Co-donor and Lead Donor will do their utmost to reach a common position on how to handle situations where the Co-donor and/or Lead Donor consider that their contributions have not been or will not be used and/or accounted for by the Fund as provided for in the Framework Agreement, If a common position cannot be reached, the Co-donor may request the Lead

Donor to take the following measures, without prejudice to any other measures

• Freeze/suspend any future disbursement of Co-donor contributions to the

Fund;

• Recover some or all of the funds already disbursed to the Lead Donor that have not already been irrevocably committed in good faith by the Lead Donor to a third party;

• Cancel the Addendum to the Framework Agreement which covers the Codonor's contribution to the Fund and has given rise to this arrangement.

6.2. If the Donors are unable to reach a common position on how to handle these situations, the Co-donor may, without prejudice to any other measures:

Freeze/suspend any future disbursement to the Lead Donor;

• Recover any contribution transferred to the Lead Donor that has not been disbursed to the Fund;

• Request, in respect of its own contribution, that the Lead Donor take any measure mentioned in point 1 above against fund recipients.

